<item>
            <title>[HBASE-5089] NIO based REST server</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5089</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Rest server code uses Jetty 6.1.26, which uses old IO (org.mortbay.jetty.Server). It would be good if Rest server uses NIO based servlet server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The options are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://download.eclipse.org/jetty/stable-8/xref/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Jetty 7 or above (NIO based)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/netty/netty/wiki/Related-projects&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Netty-based Rest server&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://grizzly.java.net&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Grizzly&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
