                            <comment id="13174850" author="stack" created="Thu, 22 Dec 2011 15:42:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13174983" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 22 Dec 2011 19:24:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cloudera ships a Jetty 6 version with NIO, drop in replacement, open source: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/toddlipcon/jetty-hadoop-fix&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/toddlipcon/jetty-hadoop-fix&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t have an opinion about what servlet server to use. Once upon a time we had a WAR target. We dropped it due to build difficulties when moving to Maven initially. We could bring it back, leave it up to the user what servlet container to use.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
